Customs finished with 30 points, followed by NSCDC -24 points, Kano pillars -23 points, police-22 points, Nigeria Immigrations Service (NIS)-19 points and UCEM team- 2 points. In the female category, NSCDC outclassed the sleek Customs ladies 3-0 (25-19, 25-23, 25-18) to dethrone them as champions. The NSCDC ladies emerged champions with 32 points, followed by Customs-28 points, Army-20 points, immigration- 10 points, Kada Emeralds- 9 points and Benue Queens- 3 points. Head Coach of the NCS male team Eric Kefas, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) after the match that his team worked hard to retain the title. Kefas assured fans that the team would go back to the drawing board to correct some of the lapses noticed, especially during the last game. According to him, the team will put up an impressive performance when they play at the continental club championship next year. “We promised to win the title at the end of the tournament, and we have done that all thanks to the Nigeria Customs Service for their support. “We are now going to shift all our attention to the continental club championship coming up next year and we promise to do the nation proud,’’ the coach said. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), reports that the premier league, which kicked off on Nov. 21, ended on Saturday. The male teams that participated in the league are NCS, NSCDC, The Nigeria Police, Kano Pillars, Plateau Rocks, UCEM and Famous Spiders. The female teams were: NCS, NSCDC, NIS, COAS-Army, Benue Queens, Delta Force and Kada Emeralds. Source: NAN Vanguard News Nigeria Volleyball Federation (NVBF) Technical Director, Martin Melandi, on Thursday said the federation was using the ongoing league to scout for young talents to replace the aging ones. April 12, 2018 In "News" Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) and Jaguar teams at the weekend ruled the 5th Korean Ambassador’s Taekwondo Championship. December 16, 2014 In "Sports" The Nigeria Custom Service (NCS) on Tuesday recorded a 3-0 victory over the Nigeria Police  in the Nigeria Volleyball Federation 2017/2018 League. April 10, 2018 In "Sports"